Stock Charts - "RUNAWAY GAPS"  
This gap type occurs in the middle of a trend, showing the urgency of the market to join the fast-moving trend. Runaway gaps propel the trend. Hence, they offer fantastic opportunities to join the trend as it continues. 
First, if a runaway gap is valid, the trend will continue unambiguously. Hence, if the trade works out, the market should not fill the gap any time soon. This observation gives us a simple yet reliable method to set a stop-loss order ‚Äì at the opposite end of the gap. 
Next, a runaway gap tends to form in the middle of a trend. This means that you can use the trending movement before the gap to project price targets. For this reason, a runaway gap is also known as a measuring gap. 
Now, let‚Äôs encapsulate these concepts into practical guidelines for trading runaway gaps. 
https://www.tradingsetupsreview.com/trading-continuation-with-runaway-gaps/
